   Investigations Division

        The Investigations Division administers the Board's criminal
     investigations program. The Division plans, organizes, directs, and
     controls all criminal investigative activities for the various tax
      programs administered by the Board. Its goals are to identify tax
   evasion problems, identify new fraud schemes, and actively investigate
    and assist in the prosecution of crimes committed by individuals who
              are violating the laws administered by the Board.
     * Fuel Tax Evasion
     * Cigarette and Tobacco Products Tax Evasion
     * Sales Tax Evasion
     * Frequently Asked Questions & Answers About Tax Evasion Complaints
     * File A Tax Evasion Complaint



